OL,3,C101 MPs urge Reeves to hike gambling
OL,4,Ctaxes and scrap two child benefit limit
OL,6,FA group of 101 Labour MPs have thrown
OL,7,Ftheir weight behind a call by Gordon
OL,8,FBrown for the government to hike taxes
OL,9,Fon betting companies in order to
OL,10,Ftackle child poverty.
OL,12,FIn a letter to the chancellor, Alex
OL,13,FBallinger and Beccy Cooper of the All-
OL,14,FParty Parliamentary Group said there
OL,15,Fis a "compelling" case for a "targeted
OL,16,Flevy on harmful online gambling
OL,17,Fproducts" and that the money raised
OL,18,Fshould be used to scrap the two-child
OL,19,Fbenefit cap.
