OL,3,C101 MPs urge Reeves to hike gambling
OL,4,Ctaxes and scrap two child benefit limit
OL,6,F"No child should be growing up in
OL,7,Fpoverty while gambling companies
OL,8,Fcontinue to enjoy record profits,"
OL,9,Fsays Alex Ballinger, MP for Halesowen.
OL,11,FHe added: "Harms from gambling place a
OL,12,Fhuge burden on our public services,
OL,13,Fcosting the Exchequer over #1 billion
OL,14,Fa year.
OL,16,F"It's time to confront these excessive
OL,17,Fprofits, reduce gambling-related harm,
OL,18,Ftackle poverty, and ensure gambling is
OL,19,Ftaxed fairly."
