OL,3,C101 MPs urge Reeves to hike gambling
OL,4,Ctaxes and scrap two child benefit limit
OL,6,FThe group of MPs believe the gambling
OL,7,Findustry in the UK is "lightly taxed"
OL,8,Fcompared with other countries, and
OL,9,Fthey want Chancellor Rachel Reeves to
OL,10,Fintroduce the changes recommended by
OL,11,Fthe Institute for Public Policy
OL,12,FResearch (IPPR), a think tank.
OL,14,FThe gambling industry currently
OL,15,Fbenefits from a complete exemption
OL,16,Ffrom VAT.
OL,18,FThe IPPR proposes increasing the tax
OL,19,Frate on the 'gross gambling yield' -
OL,20,Fthe money taken by betting companies
OL,21,Fafter winnings are paid out:
